Program: Omnibus
Title: Al Capone
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376jf8
Last Broadcast Date: 22 April 1987
Friends, colleagues and investigators of prohibition gangster Al Capone talk about the man said to be responsible for 200 murders. He never killed his customers and set up soup kitchens during the Great Drepression. Contributors include Roland V. Libonati and Rio Burke.